  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "To attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, there are typically a few requirements:\n\n1. **Shareholder Status:** You must be a shareholder of Berkshire Hathaway. This usually means owning at least one share of either Berkshire Hathaway Class A or Class B stock.\n\n2. **Proof of Ownership:** To gain entry, you generally need to provide proof of your shareholder status. This can be in the form of a proxy statement, a brokerage statement, or a shareholder meeting credential from Berkshire Hathaway.\n\n3. **Meeting Credential:** In past years, Berkshire Hathaway has sent out an \"Information Packet\" to shareholders detailing how to obtain a meeting credential. This credential is often required for admission.\n\n4. **Identification:** Attendees are typically required to present a valid photo ID along with their meeting credential.\n\n5. **Guest Policy:** Shareholders are sometimes allowed to bring guests to the meeting. However, each guest usually needs a credential or guest pass, which can be obtained through the shareholder.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check the latest information from Berkshire Hathaway as procedures and policies can change. This can typically be done by visiting their official website or reviewing any mailings or communications they send out to shareholders ahead of the meeting.",
